Cut to today, when Shewina and another Oakie have again set up camp for another page. Is it their problem that you feel it is your Tunare granted privilege to show up 10 minutes before Dyllin pops to kill him on cue? Regardless of the issue of quest monopolization, if you ain't got the stamina to stand in line, quit yer bitchin. Now, if there was an agreement between you and Shewina yesterday that you would take over the camp when she left, I have yet to hear of it from an Oakie.<br>
<br>
Are the Oaken monopolizing Dyllin Starshine? That seems to be up for debate right now. I and most other members are dead set against camp hogging. Apparently we've been holding that camp for a few days in a row now, and I've asked it to stop. I hope it will. I firmly believe that our reputation is far more important than that stinking book. <br>
<br>
Were you treated rudely? I dunno, the other parties say no, they say that you were rude to them. On a language challenged server, who can tell? I would hope that your role-playing would extend to a better performance than simply barking 'NO' in response to a simple request. <br>
<br>
It's obvious that you feel that you are an injured party in this debacle. I contend that you've mitigated any damages by publicly defaming and libelling the Order of the Oaken. <br>
<br>
